org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.fxg.dom

Class DelegateNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.fxg.dom.DelegateNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IFXGNode
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ContentPropertyNode, MaskPropertyNode, TextPropertyNode

    public class DelegateNode
extends Object
implements IFXGNode
    A special kind of relationship node that delegates the addition of child nodes to another parent node (instead of adding them to itself). An example of a delegate node is the fill child of a Rect component. In the snippet below, a SolidColor fill is added directly to the Rect - the parent of the fill property node. 
     <Rect width="20" height="20">
     <fill>
         <SolidColor color="#FFCC00" />
     </fill>
 </Rect>
